Security troops in Kaduna have rescued seven kidnapped persons from bandits that invaded Ungwan Garama in Chikun Local Government. It was gathered that a distress call was received from the area and security forces swiftly responded by engaging the bandits. The Commissioner Internal Security and Home Affairs Samuel Aruwan, who disclosed this in a statement said that the superior firepower of the troops forced the criminals to flee. Our Ban On Movement Of Cattle, Eating Of Beef In S-East Stands —… NFF Dumps Paseiro, Retains Eguavoen As Super Eagles Interim… He explained that the security forces exploited the escape route of the bandits, and were able to rescue seven persons who had been abducted. Aruwan said all of the rescued victims have been reunited with their families, adding that Governor Nasir El-Rufa’i commended the security forces for their spirited efforts and speed of response.